<item>
            <title>[SPARK-17805] sqlContext.read.text() does not work with a list of paths</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-17805</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I try to load multiple text files with the sqlContext, I get the&lt;br/&gt;
following error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spark-2.0.0-bin-hadoop2.4/python/lib/pyspark.zip/pyspark/sql/readwriter.py&quot;,&lt;br/&gt;
line 282, in text&lt;br/&gt;
UnboundLocalError: local variable &apos;path&apos; referenced before assignment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the code&lt;br/&gt;
(&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/sql/readwriter.py#L291&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/sql/readwriter.py#L291&lt;/a&gt;),&lt;br/&gt;
the variable &apos;path&apos; is not set if the argument is not a string.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Laurent&lt;/p&gt;</description>
